      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Hello {first_name, \"there\"},</p><p>We're still very much riding the first wave of analysis from the <em>Digital News Report</em> that launched yesterday - but there's at least one good read and one good listen below that isn't based on that.</p><p>Thanks to everyone who got in contact with responses to yesterday's piece of analysis - you've given me plenty to think about, research — and write.</p><p>Adam</p>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Journalists on social media: a reappraisal",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "3.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It's clear we're about to go through a reassessment of how journalists should behave on social media — and Twitter in particular. This came up in passing during the discussion about the ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Reuters Institute Digital News Report",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " yesterday, and is in the news again today:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.pressgazette.co.uk/just-stop-it-news-execs-will-lewis-and-lionel-barber-condemn-journalists-unbecoming-use-of-social-media-to-share-opinions/",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.pressgazette.co.uk/just-stop-it-news-execs-will-lewis-and-lionel-barber-condemn-journalists-unbecoming-use-of-social-media-to-share-opinions/",
          "title": "‘Just stop it’: News execs Will Lewis and Lionel Barber condemn journalists’ ‘unbecoming’ use of social media to share opinions - Press Gazette",
          "description": "Two senior newspaper executives have condemned journalists’ “unbecoming” use of social media to share their opinions and exclusive content. Will Lewis, the former boss of Dow Jones and the Wall Street Journal, and ex-Financial Times editor Lionel Barber have also spoken of their uneasiness about the…",
          "author": "William Turvill",
          "publisher": "Press Gazette",
          "thumbnail": "https://www.pressgazette.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/William-Lewsi-CEO-DOw-Jones1-e1581423314215.png",
          "icon": "https://www.pressgazette.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Press-Gazette-Twitter-Facebook-LOGO-300x300.jpg"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "I've had a couple of interesting discussions about the ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "collapse in trust in journalism",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/2020/06/resuters-digital-news-report-2020/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " over the past 24 hours, and one of the (many) causes several people pinpointed was the blurring of news and opinion both in publications, but especially on social media. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "This doesn't have to be the case. There are several journalists I admire — and, in some cases, know personally — whose politics are a mystery to me. They maintain an active and useful social media presence without joining in the open political warfare that exists on Twitter. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "And then there are people like ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Owen Jones",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://twitter.com/OwenJones84?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " or ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Tom Harwood",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://twitter.com/tomhfh?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " who are far more polemicists than journalists in the traditional sense. The solution lies far more with the \"political blank states\" than it does with the political outriders, and it's important we have this conversation right now. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The damage this is doing to the reputation of journalism as a profession needs addressing. And it's making social media an ever-more toxic environment for all journalists. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
