          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Big, big fan of this approach to sweating the archives. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://voices.media/la-times-audience-engagement-editor-adriana-lacy-on-using-archival-content-to-contextualise-current-events/",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://voices.media/la-times-audience-engagement-editor-adriana-lacy-on-using-archival-content-to-contextualise-current-events/",
          "title": "LA Times Audience Engagement Editor Adriana Lacy on using archival content to contextualise current events - Media Voices Podcast",
          "description": "This week, we hear from Adriana Lacy, Audience Engagement Editor at the LA Times. She launched a dedicated Instagram account …",
          "author": "Esther Thorpe",
          "publisher": "Media Voices Podcast",
          "thumbnail": "https://voices.media/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Adriana-Lacy_icon_large.jpg",
          "icon": "https://i0.wp.com/voices.media/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/cropped-Header-image-2.jpg?fit=192%2C192&ssl=1"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Instagram to eclipse Twitter as a news source",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "3.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Probably only a surprise to journalists, who have an obsession with Twitter out of all proportion to its actual userbase, but this key finding from the Digital News Report ought to be informing more audience engagement strategies than it is. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-53050959",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-53050959",
          "title": "Instagram ‘will overtake Twitter as a news source’",
          "description": "A report finds Instagram doubled its news audience last year - and could overtake Twitter by 2021.",
          "author": "BBC News",
          "publisher": "BBC News",
          "thumbnail": "https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/branded_news/BB12/production/_112909874_gettyimages-1208999506.jpg",
          "icon": "https://static.bbc.co.uk/news/1.316.03603/apple-touch-icon.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Shame it means a greater consolidation of power in the hands of Facebook, though…",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The changing face of news podcasts",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "3.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Esther digs deep into the podcast section of the Digital News Report, and finds things like this:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "With half of all respondents saying that podcasts provide more depth and understanding than other types of media, the opportunities for publishers looking to engage their audiences on a deeper level have never been clearer.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "quote",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://whatsnewinpublishing.com/what-we-learned-about-changing-podcast-consumption-from-the-digital-news-report-2020/",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://whatsnewinpublishing.com/what-we-learned-about-changing-podcast-consumption-from-the-digital-news-report-2020/",
          "title": "What we learned about changing podcast consumption, from the Digital News Report 2020 | What’s New in Publishing | Digital Publishing News",
          "description": "The Reuters Institute’s annual Digital News Report has become a hotly anticipated release over the past few years, and more so than ever this year as the industry grapples with the impact of coronavirus. From record levels of traffic to growing mistrust and news fatigue, the report acknowledges that…",
          "author": "Esther Kezia Thorpe",
          "publisher": "What’s New in Publishing | Digital Publishing News",
          "thumbnail": "https://whatsnewinpublishing.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/screen_2x-10-3.jpg",
          "icon": "https://whatsnewinpublishing.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/WNIP_MARK.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It's only taken 15 years, but podcasts are slowly becoming a critical part of the journalistic offering…",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
